text: Sahibzada Farooq Ali (5 September 1931 â€“ 29 November 2020) was a Pakistani politician. He was the ninth Speaker of National Assembly of Pakistan from 9 August 1973 to 27 March 1977. He was born in Ghakhar Mandi, British Raj. Ali was a member of the Pakistan Peoples Party. He was a member of the assembly from 1972 to 1977. Ali died on 29 November 2020 in Multan, Pakistan at the age of 89. ==References== Category:Speakers of the National Assembly of Pakistan Category:1931 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Politicians from Punjab, Pakistan
